@startuml
title MultiThreaded Test 1 — full call sequence (S3)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "TEST_CASE" as TEST
participant "AggregatableRunner\n[Synchronization]" as RUNNER
participant "MultiThreadingScheduler\n[Utilities]" as SCHED
participant "MicroSimulator\n[Utilities]" as SIM
participant "SignalHandler\n[Utilities]" as SIG
participant "Aggregator\n[Aggregation]" as AGG
participant "ObjectHandleContainer\n[Aggregation]" as OHC
participant "RAIILogStream\n[Logging]" as LOG

== Setup ==

TEST -> AGG     : Aggregator::aggregate({tp, sched, runner, sigHand})
TEST -> SCHED   : schedule(schedulingCount, Milliseconds(0))
TEST -> RUNNER  : runAllStages()
activate RUNNER

== Stage INIT ==

RUNNER -> AGG   : getAll<IAggregateableObject>()
AGG --> RUNNER  : [tp, sched, runner, sigHand]

note over RUNNER, OHC : notifyAggregationOnUpdate called for each aggregatable
RUNNER -> OHC   : setFromAggregationIfNotSet(aggregator)
OHC -> LOG      : RAIILogStream.stream\n(CPSLOG_DEBUG — component reg)
note right of LOG : **Agg→Log:stream** [GT event 1]

RUNNER -> AGG   : getAll<IAggregateableObject>()
AGG --> RUNNER  : [tp, sched, runner, sigHand]
RUNNER -> OHC   : setFromAggregationIfNotSet(aggregator)
OHC -> LOG      : RAIILogStream.stream
note right of LOG : **Agg→Log:stream** [GT event 2]

== Scheduler thread (async) ==

note over SCHED : MultiThreadingScheduler.run() spawns\nthread pool; runSchedule() dispatches tasks

SCHED -> LOG    : RAIILogStream.stream\n(CPSLOG_DEBUG — task dispatch ×multiple)
note right of LOG : **Util→Log:stream** [GT events 4–12, ×9 total\nfrom runSchedule + MicroSimulator]

SIM -> LOG      : RAIILogStream.stream\n(CPSLOG_DEBUG — simulator events)

== Stage NORMAL ==

RUNNER -> AGG   : getAll<IAggregateableObject>()
note right of RUNNER : additional notifyAggregationOnUpdate\ncycles during NORMAL stage

== Stage FINAL ==

RUNNER -> AGG   : getAll<IAggregateableObject>()
RUNNER --> TEST : runAllStages() returns

deactivate RUNNER

== Teardown ==

TEST -> SIG     : ~SignalHandler()
TEST -> SCHED   : ~MultiThreadingScheduler()
SCHED -> LOG    : RAIILogStream.stream\n(CPSLOG_DEBUG — shutdown)
SIM -> LOG      : RAIILogStream.stream\n(CPSLOG_DEBUG — stop)

@enduml
